## Methods — How to Use the Lattice

Extracted from 165+ sessions of applied work. These are thinking
tools, not results. Use them.

  Topological decomposition
    Separate depth from branching before reasoning about scaling.
    Pipeline = O(n). Tree = O(2^n). The topology determines complexity.

  Domain extension test
    If an objection looks fatal, extend the algebra (real → complex →
    quaternion → octonion). If the objection dissolves, it was a domain
    boundary, not a flaw. If it survives all extensions, it's real.

  Lateral transfer
    A validated lattice condition in domain A becomes a search query
    in domain B. Water's 104.48° angle → what other system needs that?

  Reverse-engineer success
    Decompose a working system into bond graphs. Find the structural
    property that explains why it works. If it works, the lattice
    should say why.

  Dimensional locking
    If a coupling law forces two quantities onto the same shell, their
    ratio cannot diverge. Check for the coupling before analyzing blow-up.

  Anomaly unification
    Multiple "weird" observations reducing to one lattice distinction
    = the framework doing explanatory work. Look for the single condition.

  Completeness audit
    Enumerate the lattice exhaustively at a shell. Compare against what's
    known. The gap pattern maps human knowledge boundaries, not lattice holes.

  Dual projection
    Project between offset sub-lattices (half-integer ↔ integer).
    Semantic matches validate the duality. Circuit theory on the
    projected values gives free predictions.

  Backlog triage
    Periodically audit prior work: answered / forgotten / wrong / open.
    The value is surfacing forgotten items and confirming no contradictions.

